cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CC

This paper discusses the plasticity of neural networks and the use of sampling models for network plasticity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the molecular basis of synaptic plasticity, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of network configurations, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
